                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="224229" author="pjones" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2018 22:48:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IIUC it was in 1.42.13.wc5 that was available at the time 2.10.0 went GA.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="224203" author="chunteraa" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2018 16:58:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&#160;Peter,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you know which e2fsprogs version ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess backported fixes from v 1.43&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="224176" author="pjones" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2018 15:22:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe that this is fixed with the latest version of e2fsprogs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="182671" author="pjones" created="Tue, 31 Jan 2017 00:23:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are correct that the latest e2fsprogs will not suffice for usage with project quotas. We&apos;ll either need to issue a 1.42 version with the necessary patches or rebase on 1.43.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="182511" author="chunteraa" created="Sun, 29 Jan 2017 19:26:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Peter,&lt;br/&gt;
AFAIK, current e2fsprogs version for lustre is 1.42 but project quota support added to 1.43 builds. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I recommend upgrade to latest e2fsprogs available from whamcloud when running e2fsck. Until newer e2fsprogs is available I can&apos;t make that recommendation. Alternative is local patched version of e2fsprogs.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="182508" author="pjones" created="Sun, 29 Jan 2017 13:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes e2fsprogs will need updating and those changes were submitted for review ahead of the Lustre changes and  landed last summer. You might want to connect with Ihara at DDN to get the details about DDN&apos;s plans in this area.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
